The paper deals with differential privacy and empirical risk minimization, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses privacy analysis, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper applies its approach to regularized linear and logistic regression, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
